@startuml
title Login Flow (As-Is)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

actor User
participant "Auth Page\n(Auth.jsx)" as AuthPage
participant "AuthContext" as AuthCtx
participant "frontend/services/api.js\n(Axios + Interceptor)" as FEAPI
participant "FastAPI\n/api/auth/login" as AuthRoute
participant "auth.py" as AuthAPI
database "PostgreSQL/SQLite\nusers" as DB
collections "Browser localStorage" as LS

User -> AuthPage: Submit username + password
AuthPage -> AuthCtx: login(username, password)
AuthCtx -> FEAPI: login(username, password)
FEAPI -> AuthRoute: POST /api/auth/login (JSON)
AuthRoute -> AuthAPI: parse_login_credentials()
AuthAPI -> DB: Find user by username/email
DB --> AuthAPI: User row / null

alt Invalid credentials
  AuthAPI --> FEAPI: 401 Unauthorized
  FEAPI --> AuthCtx: throw error.detail
  AuthCtx --> AuthPage: show login error
else Valid credentials
  AuthAPI -> AuthAPI: verify_password()
  AuthAPI -> DB: update last_login + commit
  AuthAPI -> AuthAPI: create_access_token()\ncreate_refresh_token()
  AuthAPI --> FEAPI: 200 {access_token, refresh_token, user}
  FEAPI -> LS: saveAuthSession()
  FEAPI --> AuthCtx: return token + user
  AuthCtx --> AuthPage: setUser(user)
  AuthPage -> AuthPage: navigate(from || "/")
end

note right of FEAPI
When protected API returns 401:
- interceptor calls /api/auth/refresh
- retries original request if refresh success
- clears session + redirect /auth if refresh fails
end note

@enduml
